KW  - Community bank
KW  - Relationship lending
KW  - Idiosyncratic risk
KW  - Market risk
KW  - Geographic diversification
KW  - Local economic shocks
AB  - The number of US community banks is falling rapidly. Is this reduction being driven in part by banks’ desire to geographically diversify to reduce their vulnerability to local economic shocks? A comparison of the performance of banks in counties that suffered economic shocks in the 1990s with similar banks in counties that did not suffer economic shocks shows that banks withstand local economic shocks quite well. This result suggests that the geographic concentration risk that community banks must bear to focus on relationship lending is small and is not an important factor contributing to the decline of community banks.
ER  - 
